11/04/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The southern town of Turnu Magurele is hosting a European conference on the role of local authorities in protecting the environment and managing hydro graphic basins.
The forum will tackle projects in countries located on the Danube River and exchange experiences with authorities involved in environment protection initiatives on the Rhine River.
In other news, the National Commission for Romania's integration in NATO met Thursday to discuss an action plan for joining the alliance, following last month's signing of accession protocols.
(Rompres, Nine O'clock - 11/04/03)
